    "extra_descs": [
      {
        "desc": "   The blade of the sword is a full meter long, and straight as an arrow, with\nlightly fluted sides.  Both edges keened down to perfect lines, invisibly sharp.\nPerfection like this could of only been forged by a god.  The black hilt is\ncontrasted only by the faint symbol of a white arrow.  Upon the blade is\nengraved a poem:\n\n                      Farslayer howls across the world\n                      For thy heart, for thy heart, who hast wronged me!\n                      Vengeance is his who casts the blade\n                      Yet he will in the end no triumph see.",
        "keywords": [
          "sword"
        ]
      }
